This paper is about a learning algorithm for decision problems modeled as extensive games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The algorithm discussed is Counterfactual Regret Minimization (CFR), which is a popular algorithm in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the trade-off between regret and memory, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and optimization (cs.SI).
